        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 2:24PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 224 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Livermore, or 22 miles northwest of Fort Collins, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wellington, Livermore, Teds Place, Poudre Park, Bellvue,
Mishawaka, Laporte, Owl Canyon, Buckeye and Waverly.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
